Bought this game only to find it doesn't work on my version of Android. Emailed and requested na refund, and still waiting for a response.

Badly needs updated. Running Android 9 on my phone: Graphics are glitchy (red blocky patches when viewing mission objectives), water is 99% invisible unless you're well under 100 feet in altitude. Lite version, which is FREE, has no issues at all. Only downside to lite is inability to play user scenarios, but they're full of the above mentioned glitches anyway. Love the Rortos flight engine (have Extreme Landings and RFS installed) but this one needs updated before I can add it for good.
Don't charge money for stuff that isn't going to work on newer devices.

I already purchased air navy fighters (non Xperia) version years ago. This is one of my favourite games and have played it everyday for years. But I see no real game improvement in this Xperia version apart from the F18's dark skin. I was hoping for air fighters quality in improvement but theres really not much change, so Ive requested a refund, sorry. World online scenario search is still very bad. My suggestion; combine all the best parts of Navy Fighters and Air Fighters into a single ultimate Game

This flight SIM is great fun, and the ability to create your own scenarios is amazing. The only observation is that the colours used on the radar/compass ie the green colour used is difficult to see & the cursor indicator could be a little bigger or a different colour. It'd be nice also if there were one or two planes extra, maybe F22 Raptor and/or F15 Striker. Otherwise great game. Carry on! :0)
